message.content:
Below is a worked‐example of how one can “read off” the target model and then pick and place the correct pieces from the dictionary without rotating them any further.  

1)  ANALYSIS OF THE MAIN IMAGE  
•  Overall Count:  The model uses a total of 13 blocks.  
   –  Left “car” structure (4 blocks):  
      –  Two horizontal orange cylinders serving as wheels.  
      –  One yellow rectangular prism bridging those wheels.  
      –  One blue cube resting on top.  
   –  Right “tower” structure (9 blocks):  
      –  Four vertical orange cylinders (two stacked in the center forming a tall tower, plus one each out to the side/back to support a “crossbeam”).  
      –  Two yellow rectangular prisms at right angles, forming the cross‐shaped platform.  
      –  Three orange “roof” wedges (one atop the tower, two perched on the crossbeam).  
•  Layering:  In broad terms there are three “heights.”  
   –  Bottom Layer:  Car wheels (horizontal cylinders) on the left, and the tower’s first‐level cylinders on the right.  
   –  Middle Layer:  The car’s yellow platform (with a cube above it) and, on the tower side, the second‐level cylinder plus the two yellow crossbeam blocks.  
   –  Top Layer:  The blue cube on the car and the three orange roof‐wedges on the tower side.  

2)  SELECTING THE CORRECT BLOCKS FROM THE DICTIONARY  
•  From the Dictionary Image, the needed indices and how many of each are:  
   –  #1 (Blue Cube) … 1×  
   –  #5 (Yellow Rectangular Block, horizontal orientation) … 2×  
       (one for the car platform, one for one arm of the tower’s cross)  
   –  #6 (Yellow Rectangular Block, perpendicular orientation) … 1×  
       (the other arm of the tower’s cross)  
   –  #8 (Orange Cylinder, vertical orientation) … 4×  
       (the tower columns: two stacked in the center, two single‐height columns to the side/back)  
   –  #9 (Orange Cylinder, horizontal orientation) … 2×  
       (the “car wheels”)  
   –  #14 (Orange “Roof” Wedge in the correct left‐to‐right ridge orientation) … 3×  

3)  SUGGESTED STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY  
{
  Step1:  Move block with index 9      //1st horizontal cylinder (car wheel)  
  Step2:  Move block with index 9      //2nd horizontal cylinder (car wheel)  
  Step3:  Move block with index 5      //Yellow platform on top of car wheels  
  Step4:  Move block with index 1      //Blue cube on the car platform  

  Step5:  Move block with index 8      //Base cylinder of main tower  
  Step6:  Move block with index 8      //Second cylinder stacked for tower  
  Step7:  Move block with index 8      //Side/back cylinder #1  
  Step8:  Move block with index 8      //Side/back cylinder #2  

  Step9:  Move block with index 5      //First yellow crossbeam (horizontal)  
  Step10: Move block with index 6      //Second yellow crossbeam (perpendicular)  

  Step11: Move block with index 14     //Roof wedge over tower  
  Step12: Move block with index 14     //First roof wedge on crossbeam  
  Step13: Move block with index 14     //Second roof wedge on crossbeam  
}

Using the above parts in exactly these orientations (no extra rotation) reproduces the target scene.
